sometimes the ObjectMap.Entries class skips an entry during iteration after removing an previous entry with ObjectMap.Entries.remove(). Here is an example:

```
    public static void main (String[] args) throws Exception {
        ObjectMap map = new ObjectMap();
        while (true) {
            int size = 1000;

            while (map.size < size) {
                map.put(MathUtils.random(), null );
            }

            int counter = 0;

            for (ObjectMap.Entries entries = map.entries(); entries.hasNext(); ) {
                counter++;
                entries.next();
                if (MathUtils.randomBoolean() ) {
                    entries.remove();
                }
            }

            if (counter != size) {
                throw new Exception("counter != size: " + counter);
            } else {
                System.out.println(counter);
            }
        }
    }
```

